  {
    "slug": "rubric_the_liturgy_of_the_palms_anglican",
    "name": "Rubric (The Liturgy of the Palms)",
    "liturgy_name": "Palm Sunday",
    "liturgy_slug": "palm_sunday_anglican",
    "kind": "rubric",
    "body_text": "During the procession, all hold branches in their hands, and appropriate hymns, psalms, or anthems are sung, such as the hymn \"All glory, laud, and honor\" and Psalm 118:19-29. At a suitable place, the procession may halt while the following or some other appropriate Collect is said",
    "section": "The Liturgy of the Palms",
    "source_file": "palmsunday.html",
    "page_number": 270,
    "raw_metadata": {
      "liturgy_name": "Palm Sunday",
      "liturgy_slug": "palm_sunday_anglican",
      "section": "The Liturgy of the Palms",
      "kind": "rubric",
      "source_file": "palmsunday.html",
      "page_number": 270,
      "speaker": null,
      "psalm_number": null,
      "verse_number": null,
      "is_optional": false
    }
  },
  {
    "slug": "text_the_liturgy_of_the_palms_anglican",
    "name": "Text (The Liturgy of the Palms)",
    "liturgy_name": "Palm Sunday",
    "liturgy_slug": "palm_sunday_anglican",
    "kind": "prayer-body",
    "body_text": "Almighty God, whose most dear Son went not up to joy but first he suffered pain, and entered not into glory before he was crucified: Mercifully grant that we, walking in the way of the cross, may find it none other than the way of life and peace; through Jesus Christ our Lord. Amen.",
    "section": "The Liturgy of the Palms",
    "source_file": "palmsunday.html",
    "page_number": 271,
    "raw_metadata": {
      "liturgy_name": "Palm Sunday",
      "liturgy_slug": "palm_sunday_anglican",
      "section": "The Liturgy of the Palms",
      "kind": "prayer-body",
      "source_file": "palmsunday.html",
      "page_number": 271,
      "speaker": null,
      "psalm_number": null,
      "verse_number": null,
      "is_optional": false
    }
  },
  {
    "slug": "rubric_the_liturgy_of_the_palms_anglican",
    "name": "Rubric (The Liturgy of the Palms)",
    "liturgy_name": "Palm Sunday",
    "liturgy_slug": "palm_sunday_anglican",
    "kind": "rubric",
    "body_text": "In the absence of a bishop or priest, the preceding service may be led by a deacon or lay reader. At services on this day other than the principal celebration, suitable portions of the preceding may be used.",
    "section": "The Liturgy of the Palms",
    "source_file": "palmsunday.html",
    "page_number": 271,
    "raw_metadata": {
      "liturgy_name": "Palm Sunday",
      "liturgy_slug": "palm_sunday_anglican",
      "section": "The Liturgy of the Palms",
      "kind": "rubric",
      "source_file": "palmsunday.html",
      "page_number": 271,
      "speaker": null,
      "psalm_number": null,
      "verse_number": null,
      "is_optional": false
    }
  },
  {
    "slug": "rubric_at_the_eucharist_anglican",
    "name": "Rubric (At the Eucharist)",
    "liturgy_name": "Palm Sunday",
    "liturgy_slug": "palm_sunday_anglican",
    "kind": "rubric",
    "body_text": "When the Liturgy of the Palms immediately precedes the Eucharist, the celebration begins with the Salutation and Collect of the Day.",
    "section": "At the Eucharist",
    "source_file": "palmsunday.html",
    "page_number": 271,
